- **Name: Implement Atoi**
- **Platform:  gfg**
- **Difficulty: medium**
- **Topic/ pattern :String parsing**

## **ğŸ”¹ Problem Understanding:**

convert string to int 

S = â€œ123â€ o/p â€”> 123

s = â€œ-â€ o/p â€”> 0

s = â€œ-0012gfgâ€ â€”>  12

## **ğŸ”¹ Approach / Logic:**

1. skip spaces
    1. s.charAt(i) == â€˜ â€˜ i++;
2. check sign 
    1. if â€˜+â€™ == 1
    2. â€˜-â€™ == -1
3. covert to digit
    1. Character.isDigit(s.charAt(i))
    2. digit = s.charAt(i)-â€™0â€™  
4. check overflow 
    1. 
    If `result > (Integer.MAX_VALUE - digit) / 10`, overflow will happen.
    
5. return result* sign 

## **ğŸ”¹ Edge Cases:**

**ğŸ”¹ Code:**

```java
java
CopyEdit
// Your Java solution here
class Solution {
    public int myAtoi(String s) {
        // Your code here
        int n = s.length();
        int sign = 1;
        int result = 0;
        int max = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        int min = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        int i = 0;
        while(i < n && s.charAt(i) == ' ' ) i++; 
            if(i<n && (s.charAt(i)== '+' || s.charAt(i) == '-')){
                if(s.charAt(i) == '-'){
                    sign = -1;
                }else if(s.charAt(i) == '+'){
                    sign = 1;
                }
                i++;
            }
        while(i < n && Character.isDigit(s.charAt(i))){
            int digit = s.charAt(i) - '0';
            if(result>(max -digit)/10){
                if(sign == 1){
                    return max;
                }else{
                    return min;
                }
            }
            result = (result * 10) + digit;
            i++;
        }
        return result*sign;
    }
}

```

